>> Hi Grant, Thank you for your recent email and for the summary of our =
meeting. I appreciate your efforts to move the claim forward. There are =
a few important matters I=E2=80=99d like to clarify to ensure the =
process remains safe, fair, and aligned with
>> Hi Grant,
>>=20
>> Thank you for your recent email and for the summary of our meeting. I =
appreciate your efforts to move the claim forward.
>>=20
>> There are a few important matters I=E2=80=99d like to clarify to =
ensure the process remains safe, fair, and aligned with Tower=E2=80=99s =
responsibilities under the policy.
>>=20
>> First, regarding the items I took with me from the property =E2=80=94 =
including my electric vehicle (EV), laptops, tablets, and mobile phones =
=E2=80=94 these were all exposed to heat, smoke, and corrosive chemicals =
(including nearby spa products that intensified the fire). I remain =
concerned about internal damage, particularly to lithium batteries, and =
the potential for delayed failure or fire.
>>=20
>> It is not appropriate or reasonable for Tower to shift the =
responsibility for assessing or managing the risk of these items to me. =
Ensuring they are safe for continued use is a critical safety issue =E2=80=
=94 not just a claims matter. Tower must take responsibility for =
confirming whether these items are safe, and whether they require =
restoration or replacement.
>>=20
>> Second, I would appreciate clarification of Asset Restore=E2=80=99s =
scope. Is their role limited to cataloguing and removing contents, or =
will they also be undertaking removal of fire- or smoke-damaged linings =
(such as jib and other non-structural internal components)? This detail =
is important for understanding when and how a proper structural =
assessment of the property will take place.
>>=20
>> Lastly, I would like to request a clear and updated plan for the =
progression of the house claim. Could you please provide:
>>=20
>> A current status update on the structural assessment and any scoping =
completed to date;
>> A proposed timeline for the next phases: removal, scoping, approvals, =
tendering, and repair;
>> Confirmation of the parties responsible for each stage and how =
updates will be communicated.
>> I look forward to your response addressing the points above.
>>=20
>> Kind regards,
>> Rafaella
>>=20
>> Let me know if you want to attach the policy wording or include any =
references to specific clauses.
>>=20
>>=20
>>=20
>>=20
>>=20
