reference and review. I received these from ASURNZ o Friday 5th =
September. =20
>>>=20
>>> Given the seriousness of the fire, and the chemical involvement =
(including spa chemicals with corrosive chlorides and bromides), I am =
concerned that critical risks may be under-assessed. Could you please =
clarify why Tower would not support me in engaging independent =
engineers, hygienists, or other specialists to provide an impartial =
view? We can provide independent swab-testing by a forensic scientist, =
which tests for chemical contamination which has occurred from the fire. =
I would need to meet with you to have you provide context and detail on =
exactly what chemicals were present and where they were located within =
the property. I am happy to progress this process further with you as =
soon as possible =E2=80=93 but I will need to establish more context and =
detail as to what this potential contamination may be, before we =
undertake any testing. We can also share the methodology of the forensic =
testing with you before we undertake the testing.  =20
>>>=20
>>> Further, I request that I be included in all communications with any =
assessors and 3rd parties=E2=80=94 including texts, emails, calls, and =
meetings =E2=80=94 and that these be scheduled so I have the opportunity =
to participate. This is essential for transparency and to ensure I am =
properly informed about the basis of decisions being made. I can =
accommodate this as much as is practically possible. I have kept you =
fully informed of every step and process that I have undertaken to date =
when progressing your claim. I understand that you have made a privacy =
request to our claims department =E2=80=93 which will provide you with =
access to all communications regarding your claim. I will forward this =
request that you have made to a Senior Claims Manager =E2=80=93 so that =
they can respond to your request in a more comprehensive response. This =
is a Claims Management request =E2=80=93 whereas my focus is on the =
structural repairs required for your claim. Please allow to forward and =
escalate this request for you.   =20
>>>=20
>>> 2. Structural elements =E2=80=93 linings and framing
>>>=20
>>> You mentioned that, in addition to demolishing and rebuilding the =
closed deck, your intention is to replace only a couple of structural =
beams and to rely on methods such as dry-ice blasting and thermal =
fogging for the bricks. =46rom a technical perspective, this seems =
inadequate because:
>>>=20
>>> Smoke odour and residue remain even on the first floor =E2=80=94 the =
least affected part of the house =E2=80=94 three months after the fire, =
suggesting deep penetration.=20
>>> The fire involved spa chemicals, creating corrosive residues =
(chlorides, bromides) likely absorbed into linings, timber framing, and =
fixings. I have responded to this as above.
>>> Superficial cleaning, fogging, or painting over residues cannot =
ensure long-term safety or durability.
>>> Bricks and mortar are porous: once penetrated by smoke and chemical =
residues, they can continue to off-gas and deteriorate over time, =
undermining both habitability and structural performance.
>>> =20
>>> Similarly, timber framing, structural timbers, and plasterboard =
linings are fibrous and absorbent. Once smoke and chemical residues =
penetrate, they may release odours, compromise air quality, accelerate =
corrosion of embedded fixings, and create conditions for hidden mould or =
decay. These risks cannot be fully eliminated by surface cleaning
>>> Your approach appears to focus only on visible damage (e.g. darkened =
beams), while overlooking non-visible but equally serious fire, smoke, =
and water impacts. This is not appropriate, creates significant =
long-term risks, and is not aligned with Tower=E2=80=99s obligation to =
reinstate the house to an =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D standard.
>>> On that basis, could you clarify how retaining contaminated bricks, =
timbers, and linings meets Tower=E2=80=99s obligation to reinstate the =
property to a =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D standard? What testing and =
certification is planned to ensure these critical services are restored =
to a safe and =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D condition?
>>> =20
>>> 3. Roof assessment
>>> You indicated that the roof requires no work. I find this difficult =
to reconcile with the evidence: [ with respect I said that there was no =
