and aligned with</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p></div></div></div><p><spa=
n style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Helvetica">Hi =
Grant,</span></p><p><span =
style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Helvetica">Thank you for your =
recent email and for the summary of our meeting. I appreciate your =
efforts to move the claim forward.</span></p><p><span =
style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Helvetica">There are a few =
important matters I=E2=80=99d like to clarify to ensure the process =
remains safe, fair, and aligned with Tower=E2=80=99s responsibilities =
under the policy.</span></p><p><span =
style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Helvetica">First, regarding the =
items I took with me from the property =E2=80=94 including my electric =
vehicle (EV), laptops, tablets, and mobile phones =E2=80=94 these were =
all exposed to heat, smoke, and corrosive chemicals (including nearby =
spa products that intensified the fire). I remain concerned about =
internal damage, particularly to lithium batteries, and the potential =
for delayed failure or fire.</span></p><p><span =
style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Helvetica">It is not appropriate or =
reasonable for Tower to shift the responsibility for assessing or =
managing the risk of these items to me. Ensuring they are safe for =
continued use is a critical safety issue =E2=80=94 not just a claims =
matter. Tower must take responsibility for confirming whether these =
items are safe, and whether they require restoration or =
replacement.</span></p><p><span =
style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Helvetica">Second, I would =
appreciate clarification of Asset Restore=E2=80=99s scope. Is their role =
limited to cataloguing and removing contents, or will they also be =
undertaking removal of fire- or smoke-damaged linings (such as jib and =
other non-structural internal components)? This detail is important for =
understanding when and how a proper structural assessment of the =
property will take place.</span></p><p><span =
style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Helvetica">Lastly, I would like to =
request a clear and updated plan for the progression of the house claim. =
Could you please provide:</span></p><ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" =
start=3D"1" type=3D"1"><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l9 =
level1 lfo12"><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:Helvetica">A =
current status update on the structural assessment and any scoping =
