please clarify the following so I can properly understand the =
approach</span><span style=3D"font-size: =
12pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></div></div><p>Hi Grant,</p><p>I am following =
up on our visit to the property on Tuesday. I left the meeting feeling =
quite confused about several points, and I would be grateful if you =
could please clarify the following so I can properly understand the =
approach Tower is taking:</p><p><b>1. Independent expert =
testing</b></p><p>You indicated that Tower/you will not pay for any =
expert testing as part of my preparation of the claim, as you said that =
is what you are already doing. However, I am struggling to understand =
this position. =46rom my perspective, you are preparing the claim from =
Tower=E2=80=99s side, and I have not been invited to or involved in any =
of the NZRSC<span class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(0, 112, 192);">[can you please clarify what NZRSC =
stands for? =E2=80=93 I am sorry, I am not familiar with this =
acronym]<span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>assessments or =
discussions. This does not feel independent or transparent from my =
side.<span class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(0, 112, 192);">Attached are the material damage =
Report &amp; Scope of repair works as provided by our technical Building =
consultant. These are provided to you for your reference and review. I =
received these from ASURNZ o Friday 5<sup>th</sup><span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>September. =
&nbsp;</span></p><p>Given the seriousness of the fire, and the chemical =
involvement (including spa chemicals with corrosive chlorides and =
bromides), I am concerned that critical risks may be under-assessed. =
Could you please clarify why Tower would not support me in engaging =
independent engineers, hygienists, or other specialists to provide an =
impartial view?<span class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(0, 112, 192);">We can provide independent =
swab-testing by a forensic scientist, which tests for chemical =
contamination which has occurred from the fire. I would need to meet =
with you to have you provide context and detail on exactly what =
chemicals were present and where they were located within the property. =
I am happy to progress this process further with you as soon as possible =
=E2=80=93 but I will need to establish more context and detail as to =
what this potential contamination may be, before we undertake any =
testing. We can also share the methodology of the forensic testing with =
you before we undertake the testing. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p>Further, =
I request that I be&nbsp;included in all communications with any =
assessors&nbsp;and 3rd parties=E2=80=94 including texts, emails, calls, =
and meetings =E2=80=94 and that these be scheduled so I have the =
opportunity to participate. This is essential for transparency and to =
ensure I am properly informed about the basis of decisions being =
made.<span class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(0, 112, 192);">I can accommodate this as much as is =
practically possible. I have kept you fully informed of every step and =
process that I have undertaken to date when progressing your claim. I =
understand that you have made a privacy request to our claims department =
=E2=80=93 which will provide you with access to all communications =
regarding your claim. I will forward this request that you have made to =
a<span class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><u>Senior Claims =
Manager</u><span class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>=E2=80=93 =
so that they can respond to your request in a more comprehensive =
response. This is a Claims Management request =E2=80=93 whereas my focus =
is on the structural repairs required for your claim. Please allow to =
forward and escalate this request for you. =
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p><b>2. Structural elements =E2=80=93 =
linings and framing</b></p><p>You mentioned that, in addition to =
demolishing and rebuilding the closed deck, your intention is to replace =
only a couple of structural beams and to rely on methods such as dry-ice =
blasting and thermal fogging for the bricks. =46rom a technical =
perspective, this seems inadequate because:</p><div><ol start=3D"1" =
type=3D"1" style=3D"margin-bottom: 0in;"><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">Smoke odour and residue =
remain even on the first floor =E2=80=94 the least affected part of the =
house =E2=80=94 three months after the fire, suggesting deep =
penetration.<span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li =
class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: =
Aptos, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">The fire involved =
spa chemicals, creating corrosive residues (chlorides, bromides) likely =
absorbed into linings, timber framing, and fixings.<span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"color: =
rgb(0, 112, 192);">I have responded to this as =
above.</span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">Superficial cleaning, =
fogging, or painting over residues cannot ensure long-term safety or =
durability.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin:=
 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">Bricks and mortar are porous: once penetrated =
by smoke and chemical residues, they can continue to off-gas and =
deteriorate over time, undermining both habitability and structural =
performance.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: =
12pt;">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">Similarly, timber framing, =
structural timbers, and plasterboard linings are fibrous and absorbent. =
Once smoke and chemical residues penetrate, they may release odours, =
compromise air quality, accelerate corrosion of embedded fixings, and =
create conditions for hidden mould or decay. These risks cannot be fully =
eliminated by surface cleaning<o:p></o:p></span></li><li =
class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: =
Aptos, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">Your approach =
appears to focus only on visible damage (e.g. darkened beams), while =
overlooking non-visible but equally serious fire, smoke, and water =
impacts. This is not appropriate, creates significant long-term risks, =
and is not aligned with Tower=E2=80=99s obligation to reinstate the =
house to an =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D =
standard.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ol></div><div><div style=3D"margin: =
0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">On that basis, could you clarify how =
retaining contaminated bricks, timbers, and linings meets Tower=E2=80=99s =
obligation to reinstate the property to a =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D =
standard? What testing and certification is planned to ensure these =
critical services are restored to a safe and =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D =
condition?<o:p></o:p></span></div></div><div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></div></div><div><div =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><b><span style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">3. Roof =
assessment</span></b><span style=3D"font-size: =
12pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></div></div><p>You indicated that the roof =
requires no work. I find this difficult to reconcile with the =
evidence<span style=3D"color: rgb(0, 112, 192);">: [ with respect I said =
that there was no structural fire damage in the roof space. It could be =
accepted that there is a faint smoke odour in the roof space from any =
smoke which may have passed through this space. We have allowed for =
replacement of 95 sqm of ceiling insulation to eliminate the possibility =
of any smoke odours remaining.</span><span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><ol start=3D"1" =
type=3D"1" style=3D"margin-bottom: 0in;"><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">Large volumes of black =
smoke were seen coming out from all sides of the roof during the =
fire.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin: =
0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">A gutter was significantly =
heat-damaged.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; =
color: rgb(0, 112, 192);"><span style=3D"font-size: 12pt; color: =
windowtext;">Local reporting even suggested the fire appeared to be in =
the roof. I have been in the roof space.<span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span =
style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">There is no structural fire damage in the =
roof space.<span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></li></ol><=
p>If external heat was sufficient to damage guttering, then internal =
elements such as roof cavity insulation, underlay, battens, fixings, and =
trusses may also have been affected. Could you please clarify what =
inspection methods were used to conclude the roof was undamaged? Were =
cavity inspections, intrusive checks, or residue/chemical tests =
undertaken? What testing and certification is planned to ensure these =
critical services are restored to a safe and =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D =
condition?</p><p><b>4. Services =E2=80=93 gas, electricity, and =
water</b></p><p>I understand that you are going to test the gas unit and =
propose a plan to bring it up to new standard, which I appreciate. =
However, could you also please clarify what is planned for the =
&nbsp;electricty system, which suffered significant and widespread =
damage and the water distribution system</p><p>At present I am unclear =
how these critical services will be properly tested and reinstated. What =
testing and certification is planned to ensure these critical services =
are restored to a safe and =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D =
condition?</p><p><b>5. Timing and completeness of =
assessments</b></p><p>I am also confused and &nbsp;concerned that a =
repair plan is already being discussed before full assessments have been =
completed and before I have seen the NZRSC or other formal =
reports.</p><p>Could you clarify why Tower is progressing toward a =
repair plan at this stage rather than awaiting intrusive testing, =
particularly given the involvement of corrosive chemicals and deep smoke =
penetration? What testing and certification is planned to ensure these =
critical services are restored to a safe and =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D =
condition? And what would be the sequencing of those to inform a =
realistic plan?</p><p>In addition, is it not too risky to wait until =
after restructuring works to determine whether the house is safe and =
meets code requirements? That approach could prolong reinstatement =
unnecessarily, leaving me at greater disadvantage with accommodation =
costs and delays that are outside my control.&nbsp;</p><p><b>6. Testing =
and reporting</b></p><p>Could you please confirm:</p><ol start=3D"1" =
type=3D"1" style=3D"margin-bottom: 0in;"><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">What tests or assessments =
have actually been completed so far?<o:p></o:p></span></li><li =
class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: =
Aptos, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">Why, given the =
involvement of spa chemicals, no intrusive testing has been =
arranged?<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin: =
0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">When the NZRSC report and other reports will =
be made available to me?<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">What testing and =
certification is planned to ensure my house restored to a safe and =E2=80=9C=
as new=E2=80=9D condition? And could you please provide sequencing and =
timings.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ol><p><b>7. Accommodation support =
-<span class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></b><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(0, 112, 192);">Claims Manager will answer these =
questions for you.<span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></p><div>&nbsp;<br =
class=3D"webkit-block-placeholder"></div><p>A number of critical =
assessments remain outstanding =E2=80=94 including tests for chemical =
penetration, the roof structure and cavity, and essential services such =
as electricity and water. Until these are properly completed and =
confirmed, the house is uninhabitable.</p><p>At present, my rental =
accommodation is being funded under the contents policy ($30,000 limit). =
However, with reinstatement not yet underway and key assessments still =
pending, it is clear this allowance will be insufficient. These delays =
are entirely outside my control.</p><p>The Fair Insurance Code requires =
insurers to act fairly and not disadvantage customers through delay. The =
principle of insurance is to restore the insured to the pre-loss =
position. To avoid being placed at a further disadvantage, I would like =
to explore the following options:</p><ol start=3D"1" type=3D"1" =
style=3D"margin-bottom: 0in;"><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin: =
0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">Option A: Tower agrees I may take the lead in =
arranging necessary assessments and reinstatement works, provided all =
works are to =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D standard, meet current Building =
Code requirements, and remain within the insured sum. Tower would =
reimburse incurred costs within 15 days of invoice on a monthly basis, =
ensuring timely progress without administrative =
delay.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin: =
0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">Option B: Alternatively, Tower confirms that =
it will continue to cover my accommodation costs until the house is =
fully restored and habitable, given that ongoing delays are not of my =
making.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ol><p>Could you please confirm which of =
these approaches Tower is prepared to adopt, so that I am not unfairly =
disadvantaged by circumstances outside my control?</p><p><b>8. Privacy =
Act material =E2=80=93<span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></b><span style=3D"color: =
rgb(0, 112, 192);">Claims Manager will answer these questions for =
you.<span class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span></p><p>You =
previously referred me to information provided under the Privacy Act, =
which I could not find. I found those two email but the links I received =
do not open or function. Could you please resend this information, =
ensuring that the links are accessible, or alternatively provide the =
documents as direct PDF/email attachments?</p><p><b>Summary =
point</b></p><p>At present, I remain unclear how Tower=E2=80=99s =
proposed approach =E2=80=94 which appears to favor superficial cleaning =
and limited replacement =E2=80=94 can reasonably restore my property to =
a safe, habitable, =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D standard, particularly given =
the deep smoke and chemical penetration of bricks, timbers, and linings, =
the unresolved questions regarding the roof structure and cavity, and =
the uncertainty around full reinstatement of essential services such as =
electricity, water, and gas.</p><p>I would greatly appreciate your =
clarification on each of these points so that I can properly understand =
how my home will be restored to a safe, habitable, =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D=
 standard,</p><p>Kind regards,</p><p>Raffaella del Prete</p><div><div =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: =
12pt;">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></div></div><div><blockquote =
style=3D"margin-top: 5pt; margin-bottom: 5pt;"><div><div style=3D"margin: =
