<o:shapelayout v:ext=3D"edit">
<o:idmap v:ext=3D"edit" data=3D"1" />
</o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]--><div lang=3D"EN-US" link=3D"blue" =
vlink=3D"purple" style=3D"word-wrap:break-word"><div =
class=3D"WordSection1"><p class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span =
style=3D"">Kia ora, Grant and Claim Maager/Team,</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto">Thank you =
for proposing to bring the stakeholders together and provide a =
considered response. While I look forward to receiving written reply to =
my specific questions=E2=80=94could you please confirm when I=E2=80=99ll =
receive it and suggest a meeting date with an attendee list? &nbsp;To =
keep things professional and efficient, could we agree on clear =
deliverables and a test-led plan? To promote progress, I=E2=80=99m =
sharing my initial questions on the documents received. I haven=E2=80=99t =
obtained professional advice yet, so I reserve the right to ask further =
questions, seek clarification, and provide additional =
feedback.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><u><span =
style=3D"">Fairness &amp; participation</span></u><span =
style=3D""><br>=46rom the ASURNZ report there were two assessment =
sessions (11 and 21 August). I wasn=E2=80=99t invited to the briefings =
or either site inspection. I appreciate this may have been an oversight, =
but it leaves me without visibility of the brief given to ASURNZ and =
what they actually saw on the day.<br>To balance the process, I kindly =
propose that Tower funds an independent insured-side assessment with me =
directly engaged; and that I am permitted a one-on-one session with =
ASURNZ, as Grant had, so I can brief them directly and ask =
questions.<br>I=E2=80=99d also be grateful for the raw site notes and =
photo log from those two attendances, and for inclusion (with reasonable =
notice) in all future briefings, site visits, and =
communications.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><u><span =
style=3D"">Fire chemistry &amp; severity</span></u><span =
style=3D""><br></span><span style=3D"color:#212121">FENZ records show =
spa-pool chlorine/oxidisers stored in the origin cupboard, a HAZMAT =
requirement at dispatch, and escalation to a second alarm; ASURNZ also =
records cavity smoke migration and roof-edge heat (deformed soffit, =
melted gutter). Smoke odour remains three months later. Taken together, =
these factors indicate a heightened risk of corrosive/acidic residues =
and deep smoke penetration into cavities, fixings, the roof assembly, =
and HVAC, so a visual-only approach is not appropriate.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span =
style=3D"color:#212121">As such, could you please provide a written, =
insurer-funded plan and schedule setting out methods/standards, pass =
criteria, dates, and named leads. The detailed methodology and =
acceptance thresholds are to be designed and agreed by the appropriate =
independent experts (hygienist, CPEng structural engineer, EWRB-licensed =
electrician/inspector, certifying gasfitter and HVAC technician, =
licensed plumber, and a moisture/corrosion specialist) and laboratories. =
&nbsp;Also it is my understanding that AC2213 (Auckland Council Fire =
Reinstatement practice note) expects intrusive investigation and formal =
sign-offs where the primary structure or external moisture/fire systems =
are affected, including removal of wet linings/insulation, a CPEng =
report on the impact to the primary structure, LBP design/supervision =
where applicable, and s.112 BA04 considerations.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span =
style=3D"color:#212121">I also believe that at a minimum&nbsp;the plan =
should address intrusive verification of roof/eaves (including underlay, =
battens, fixings, and truss nail-plates, with perimeter =
residue/corrosivity checks where odour is present); cavity assessment on =
the first-floor south/west elevations and around the fireplace (with =
removal/cleaning and hygienist clearance before re-lining where =
indicated); hygiene and clearance for heat-pump heads and the roof-space =
gas unit/any ducting; whole-installation electrical verification to =
AS/NZS 3000 with certification; plumbing system integrity testing and =
disinfection where indicated; moisture logging and corrosion/pH-chloride =
screening of representative framing/fasteners and masonry; and =
independent IAQ/surface clearances before re-lining and =
re-occupation.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><u><span =
style=3D"">Scope adequacy</span></u><span style=3D""><br>=46rom the =
ASURNZ document, there was smoke migration into first-floor cavities =
with staining on the back of removed plasterboard, and roof-edge heat =
with deformed soffit sheeting and a melted gutter. The current scope =
appears focused on apparent damage (clean/smoke-seal, selective =
electrical checks, =E2=80=9Ctest &amp; recommission=E2=80=9D gas) rather =
than the real damage pathways (cavities, roof assembly, services, =
corrosion).<br>Respectfully, it is not only the visibly charred beams =
that can be compromised. Non-charred structural members, fixings, =
nail-plates, and brick/mortar exposed to smoke and/or acidic residues =
can degrade over time if not neutralised or replaced.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span =
style=3D"">Accordingly, could you please explain and =
evidence:</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><ul =
type=3D"disc"><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"">Why full removal of =
plasterboard/linings (GIB) in all areas showing cavity smoke migration =
is not proposed, given deep penetration and potential chemical =
residues.<span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li =
class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"">The evidence-based criteria being used to =
decide retain vs replace for framing, fixings, nail-plates and =
insulation (including any lab thresholds, corrosion checks, <span =
style=3D"font-size:7.5pt">or</span> moisture limits).<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"">Masonry/brickwork: why cleaning/sealing is proposed instead =
of replacement of visibly affected brickwork and repointing where =
residues or acid attack are indicated; please confirm that any =
replacement will achieve an identical visual match and quality.<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"">Framing and fixings: how non-charred but smoke-exposed =
framing and fasteners will be assessed (including corrosion and surface =
pH/chloride checks), and the criteria for replacement rather than =
sealing.<span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li =
class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"">Water/firefighting impacts: what moisture =
mapping, drying logs, mould assessment/clearance, and wet-insulation =
replacement are planned for all affected areas (including ceiling/floor =
cavities).<span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li =
class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"">Basement storage and wider basement: why =
there is no building-works scope for the storage area and other basement =
spaces when contents from those areas (including items kept in sealed =
Sistema containers) have been deemed uneconomic to restore; please =
explain the tests relied upon to consider the building surfaces in those =
same areas salvageable, and provide the decontamination/repair plan for =
those spaces.<span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li =
class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"">Deck: current scope limits works to a =
partial deck replacement when heat/char/smoke exposure is recorded, =
while Grant has indicated the full deck would be rebuilt; and the tests =
relied upon (char-depth logs, moisture readings, condition of =
fixings/hangers/ledger-to-wall, any chloride/pH screening at the =
deck-to-wall interface). Please also confirm how the deck and any =
balustrade/handrail will meet current Code requirements =
(structure/barriers) and whether producer statements or LBP supervision =
are proposed.<span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li =
class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D""><span style=3D"color:windowtext">Deck: =
current scope proposes only a partial deck replacement, although Grant =
has recently indicated the full deck would be rebuilt. Could you please =
explain how a patch repair would still achieve a result that is =
=E2=80=9Creasonably equivalent to when new=E2=80=9D in appearance, =
strength and durability? Could you please also share the results you are =
relying on for: (i) char/heat checks of boards and joists; (ii) moisture =
readings and decay risk; (iii) removal and inspection of representative =
hangers, bolts and ledger fixings for corrosion/galvanising loss; (iv) =
ledger-to-wall verification, including flashing/weep details; (v) =
chloride/pH screening at the perimeter and fixings; and (vi) =
confirmation that the balustrade/handrail meets current requirements. If =
any results do not meet the engineer=E2=80=99s acceptance criteria, then =
those components will need to be replaced so the finished deck is truly =
as-new.</span><span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li =
class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"">How each relevant element=E2=80=94whether =
included in the current scope or currently omitted (e.g., =
walls/ceilings, framing, insulation, services, roof-edge components, =
masonry/brickwork, kitchen, basement storage areas, deck, roof-space =
plant)=E2=80=94will be addressed to achieve the policy standard of =
reinstatement =E2=80=9Creasonably equivalent to when new=E2=80=9D across =
appearance, size, functionality, integrity and relative quality; and, =
for any omitted element, the objective test results and reasoning relied =
upon for omission, plus the hold-points/clearances that would trigger =
its inclusion in the scope.<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"">Kitchen: why no kitchen works are included despite the =
earlier heavy smoke staining (later cleaned by David, engaged by Tower). =
Please provide the evidence used to exclude the kitchen (noting that =
post-clean visuals are not a clearance), the documentation of the =
cleaning undertaken (before/after photos, products/methods/SDS), the =
hygienist=E2=80=99s sampling plan for cabinetry/voids/rangehood/duct, =
and the electrical/gas/plumbing checks and clearance criteria to confirm =
the kitchen is safe for normal use.<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"">Roof/eaves and roof space: given the documented melted gutter =
and deformed soffit=E2=80=94and ongoing smoke odour=E2=80=94why is there =
no intrusive roof/eaves scope? Please confirm what was actually opened =
and inspected, what (if any) residue or corrosivity testing was done at =
the eaves/perimeter, and whether underlay, battens, fixings and truss =
nail-plates were assessed. Please also state whether perimeter wipe =
sampling is planned, whether any underlay/batten/fixing replacements are =
allowed for if contamination/heat effects are found, and whether a CPEng =
will sign off any retained structural members and roof connections. As a =
gas heating unit sits in the roof space, please confirm how =
hygiene/clearance of those components and any ducting will be =
achieved.<span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li></ul><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><u><span =
style=3D"">Standard of reinstatement</span></u><span =
style=3D""><br></span><span style=3D"color:#212121">I believe that the =
policy requires that&nbsp;repairs must reinstate affected parts to a =
standard reasonably equivalent to when new (appearance, size, =
functionality, integrity, relative quality). For visible finishes such =
as brickwork, replacements should match identically in appearance and =
quality, so the final result is indistinguishable and =
durable.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><u><span =
style=3D"">Building consent &amp; AC2213</span></u><span =
style=3D""><br>ASURNZ=E2=80=99s narrative suggests no consent under =
Schedule 1/s42A. My understanding is that Auckland Council=E2=80=99s =
AC2213 indicates consent is required for substantial replacement after =
fire and expects a CPEng report addressing the primary structure =
(including nail-plates/fixings at heat-affected eaves), HVAC =
removal/servicing, replacement of wet insulation, and Energy Works =
certificates for electrical/gas.<br>Could you please:</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><ul =
type=3D"disc"><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"">Engage a CPEng for the =
primary-structure report (including the roof/eaves zone); and<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"">Obtain Council=E2=80=99s written position for the final scope =
(consent, or a specific written exemption)? If consent is required, =
please outline LBPs/Producer Statements and inspections.<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li></ul><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><u><span =
style=3D"">Decision-gate and transparency</span></u><span =
style=3D""><br>No repair work or close-ups should occur until all expert =
reports and clearances above are completed and shared, and we have =
agreed what needs to be done. Please schedule all inspections and tests =
with me present, and provide the raw lab reports and photo =
logs.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><u><span =
style=3D"">Accommodation</span></u><span style=3D""><br>Several critical =
assessments remain outstanding =E2=80=94 chemical penetration, roof =
structure/cavities, and essential services (electrical, gas, water, =
HVAC). In light of the FENZ findings and Auckland Council=E2=80=99s =
AC2213 guidance, these should have been anticipated and sequenced from =
the outset; the resulting delays were preventable and are outside my =
control. I will wait for your proposal here. Please let me know how =
Tower plans to manage accommodation while testing, any consent/design =
steps, decontamination and reinstatement proceed.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span =
style=3D"">Kindly confirm in writing:</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><ul =
type=3D"disc"><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"">When I will receive =
your written responses and the meeting date (with agenda).<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"">My inclusion in all future briefings/inspections and =
provision of prior notes/photos.<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"">The testing plan (roof/eaves, cavities, HVAC/heat pumps &amp; =
gas heating, electrical, gas, water, moisture/corrosion, IAQ) with labs, =
pass criteria, and dates.<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"">A revised scope that is test-led and targets as-new outcomes =
(not cosmetic sealing).<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"">The Council/AC2213 path and CPEng engagement (consent or =
written exemption with reasons).<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"">Temporary accommodation plan for the period until the home is =
safe and habitable.<span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li></ul><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto">Thank you =
for your cooperation and prompt attention,<o:p></o:p></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal" =
style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto"><span =
lang=3D"IT" style=3D"">Ng=C4=81 mihi,<br>Raffaella Del Prete</span><span =
lang=3D"IT" =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"IT" =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"IT" =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt">Get <a =
href=3D"https://aka.ms/GetOutlookForMac">Outlook for Mac =
</a></span><span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><div =
id=3D"mail-editor-reference-message-container"><div><div><div =
style=3D"border:none;border-top:solid #B5C4DF 1.0pt;padding:3.0pt 0in =
0in 0in"><p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-bottom:12.0pt"><b><span =
style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">From: </span></b><span style=3D"font-size: =
12pt;">Grant Metson &lt;Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz&gt;<br><b>Date: =
</b>Wednesday, 10 September 2025 at 2:03</span><span style=3D"font-size: =
12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">=E2=80=AF</span><span =
style=3D"font-size: 12pt;">PM<br><b>To: </b>Raffaella del Prete =
&lt;raffaellanz@icloud.com&gt;<br><b>Cc: </b>Claims =
&lt;Claims@tower.co.nz&gt;, Chris Cornwall =
&lt;Chris.Cornwall@tower.co.nz&gt;<br><b>Subject: </b>RE: Request for =
Clarification - Re: 23 Mays Road - progression of claims response. =
C90306048<o:p></o:p></span></p></div><p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span =
style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Hello Rafaella,</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Please see below =
<span style=3D"color:#0070C0">[in blue] </span>my responses to the =
questions in your email below dated September 6, 2025.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Please also find =
attached a copy of the =E2=80=98Material Damage Report=E2=80=99 &amp; =
the =E2=80=98Scope of Works=E2=80=99 which relates to the damage =
report.</span><span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have done my best =
to answer the specific questions that you have raised. My general =
response to your enquiries is summarised as follows:</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><ol start=3D"1" =
type=3D"1"><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"mso-list:l4 level1 =
lfo1"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">All material and documentation of =
any form, in respect of your claim, is discoverable and is available to =
be provided to you. This will remain your enduring right through-out the =
claim process.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li =
class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"mso-list:l4 level1 lfo1"><span =
style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I will need to work closely with your Claim =
Manager to ensure the information that you are requesting is provided to =
you in a timely manner. I am wiling to assist the Claims Manager in this =
respect.</span><span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li=
 class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"mso-list:l4 level1 lfo1"><span =
style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">All aspects of potential damage which you are =
seeking to receive assurances on can be responded to on an individual =
basis. I am unable to provide those responses to you in this email, as I =
will require consultation and input from the relevant specialists and =
consultants.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li></ol><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I think the most =
constructive next step would be for me to schedule a meeting with the =
key stakeholders within Tower Insurance and following that provide you =
with the clarification that you have requested.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Please allow me to =
schedule a meeting with my colleagues and take the time required to =
provide you with a considered and comprehensive response.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Best =
Regards,</span><span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Grant. </span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p =
class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p><table =
