style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p></div></div></div><div><d=
iv><div><p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have =
spoken with both our Motor and our Claims Team Leaders, and they have =
said that the items you have enquired about are very unlikely to be =
affected by the fire given their location with respect to the proximity =
of the fire. I do understand that you would like to be 100% certain that =
the lithium batteries in these items have not been affected from the =
fire. The standard process in this situation is that you can undertake =
any testing of any of your items which you wish to, to obtain test =
results or a report which your insurer can consider for inclusion in =
your claims. If the test results prove any damage or loss to these items =
from the fire =E2=80=93 then your insurer will consider them within your =
claim.</span><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p></div></div></div><div><d=
iv><div><p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span =
style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><span =
